	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Actually! I take this all back.<br /><br />The artifacts do occur on a real NES, just not every time. I think this is a PPU alignment thing where some resets it will have no artifact, and some resets you'll see a few pixels worth.<br /><br />So... actually those emulators are fine. I can make it look like that on some resets.<br /><br />(FCEUX is not a good thing to compare against for pixel perfect timings like that, even New PPU mode in FCEUX only has a granularity of 8 pixels per CPU synchronization.)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


